<div class="alert alert-info mb-4" role="alert">
    <h4 class="alert-heading"><span class="bi bi-info-circle"></span> Data & Services Sample</h4>
    <p>
        This page demonstrates async data loading with service integration, showing how ViewModels can consume 
        services via dependency injection and manage loading states in a Blazor application.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-cloud-download"></span> Data Loading Features</h6>
            <ul class="small">
                <li><strong>Service Injection:</strong> ViewModels receive services through constructor injection</li>
                <li><strong>Async Data Fetching:</strong> Data loaded in <code>OnInitializedAsync</code> lifecycle method</li>
                <li><strong>Loading State Management:</strong> UI shows loading indicator while data is being fetched</li>
                <li><strong>HttpClient Integration:</strong> Demonstrates API calls using injected HttpClient</li>
                <li><strong>Observable Collections:</strong> Dynamic data binding with automatic UI updates</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-gear"></span> How It Works</h6>
            <p class="small">
                The <code>FetchDataViewModel</code> uses <code>MvvmOwningComponentBase</code> to manage its own 
                service scope. The ViewModel receives a <code>WeatherForecastService</code> through dependency 
                injection and loads the weather data asynchronously.
            </p>
            <p class="small">
                During the initial load, the UI displays a loading message. Once the data is fetched, 
                the <code>WeatherForecasts</code> property is populated and the table is rendered. This 
                demonstrates how MVVM separates data access logic from UI concerns.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <p class="mb-0">
        <span class="bi bi-lightbulb"></span> <strong>Key Benefit:</strong> 
        Clean separation of data access logic in ViewModels with full DI support, making your Blazor 
        components testable and maintainable.
    </p>
</div>
